Description: Fragment of handle from a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff-brown. Circular stamp at top of handle with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Name Chrysostratos. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX CON 1386.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0566)
